[thinking] I'm exploring the idea of whether to use lazy initialization or not. It seems an AOT process may call a no-args main with zero parameters, so that’s something to keep in mind. I need to ensure that tests execute under Native Image by default. I might need to make existing placeholder classes public since all top-level test classes must be public. Updating the placeholder to be more meaningful seems like a good move! But I should think more about the implications of this change.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Evaluating test class structure**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering whether to remove the @Test method since it may not be relevant. The source file can be compiled even without tests, but it feels necessary to edit the class to public and potentially remove the placeholder, especially since it’s currently package-private. I could replace the whole Spring_bootTest with an active class, but the naming conventions might complicate things. Still, making it public seems like the right move, though I should also check Checkstyle guidelines about underscores in class names.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Checking class naming conventions**
[thinking] 
[thinking] The existing scaffold has a class name with an underscore, so I’m wondering if Checkstyle actually allows that. It was package-private, but making it public might still pose an issue with the naming. I think it’d be smart to check if many other public classes have underscores in their names. If that's common practice, it could be fine to keep it as is, but I want to double-check for best practices!
[thinking] 
